Former minister of Budget and National Planning, Udoma Udo Udoma has  been appointed the pro-chancellor of Akwa Ibom State University. Udoma, a former senator and lawyer is a key player in Nigeria’s corporate sector, having held the chairmanship position of many blue-chip companies. Emmanuel approved the appointment in a statement signed by Emmanuel Ekuwem, secretary to the state government and made available to newsmen in Uyo, yesterday. Udoma takes over from Samuel Inyang, who according to the statement, has stepped aside from his position. No reason was given for Inyang’s decision to step aside but findings revealed that this may not be unconnected with plans by the governor to  appoint a new vice chancellor from a particular senatorial district of the state. Udoma hails from Akwa Ibom South Senatorial District and with Inyang’s  departure, observers believe the new vice chancellor is likely to come from Akwa Ibom North West Senatorial district. The tenure of the current vice chancellor of the University, Eno Ibanga ended in April but he was reappointed in acting capacity  pending the appointment of a substantive vice chancellor. Ibanga was among the eight nominees recently cleared by the state assembly for appointment as  a member of the state executive council